rComments: Amazing professor, kind human being, and a virtuoso scholar.  One of the best.  Life changing course. Made me reconsider the entire direction of my academic career.  Thank you, Prof. Lahusen!
Wonderful professor and always selects interesting readings! Very kind person as well.

He's generally just a really great professor. His research outside of class is even more interesting and he's always willing to talk with students about it or anything else when he has the time. A really great prof.

he is an great prof very sensitive and perceptive about arguments and issues enjoyed the course interesting readings learned alot really enjoyed the movie clips segment to the course great dimension yes he can ramble at times but its always with a point and he is good guy with a passion for the topic which is most important extremely approachable!

This is the worst course. I thought Soviet Culture would be interesting. We read 300+ pages a week. And he is impossible to understand - it is all about "rayonism" and "suprematism" and other postmodern garbage. His lectures are directionless. His expectations are unrealistic. I wish I could drop it, but there are no other classes to get into.

wonderful professor.  kind, very intelligent and insightful, and a good lecturer.  talks a little fast at times, but those who have taken his class finish the term knowing substantially more they did to begin with!
Great man, smart, kind, helpful, patient... all the qualities one would want in a professor.
